##The day before the death of a 17-year-old child with cerebral palsy in Hubei, his father repeatedly called 120 and 110 for help

Micro Signal Damihexiaomi 2015

Rice and Xiaomi are the leading service platforms for children with autism spectrum in China, providing integrated services such as rehabilitation training, integrated education support, parent training, online courses and popular science consultation. At present, we have set up service organizations and many integrated kindergartens in Beijing, Shanghai, Guangzhou, Shenzhen and Zhengzhou, and will expand to more areas in the future.

At noon on January 29, Yan Cheng, a 17-year-old with cerebral palsy in Huanggang, Hubei Province, died. In the evening, news of his death hit Weibo, a popular microblogging site, and drew national attention.

On the same day, there were 170 confirmed cases of COVID-19 pneumonia in China, bringing the total to 7,711. There were 12,167 suspected cases.

Yan's single father, Yan Xiaowen, was one of the suspected cases of the plague and was confined to a hospital for six days with his second son, Xiaowei, who has autism. For six days, the dependent father and son lost touch, leaving the quadriplegic Yan at home alone for the last six lonely days of his life.

On Jan. 26, Yan, who had a fever, was taken to the hospital, where he was examined and sent home. In the end,

On the morning of January 29th, the mayor brought Yan Yan to a central settlement. But two hours later, the Father Yan Xiaowen received the news of his son's death.

The day before his death, Yan Xiaowen and his friends, who had been quarantined in the hospital ward, called Hong'an County 120 and 110 several times, begging them to admit him as soon as possible, but to no avail.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Yan Cheng before he died

Single Dad quarantined after fever

The deceased, Yan Cheng, lived in huajiahe town, Hong'an County, Hubei Province. He has cerebral palsy, Quadriplegia, mental retardation, can't talk, can't walk, can't take care of himself. He also has a 10-year-old brother with moderate autism.

His father, Yan Xiaowen, worked in a canteen in his early years. After his wife committed suicide in 2010 due to financial hardship, Yan quit his job to take care of the children. The three of them lived on the government's subsistence allowance and other people's relief, "Snail Home" , a non-profit organization that usually lives in Hankou, Wuhan.

On January 17, Yan and his two children returned from Hankou to their hometown, Yanjia village. Three days later, Yan Xiaowen developed fever and started to go to the hospital for an intravenous drip. On Jan. 22, Yan Xiaowen, who attended the Huajiahe Township Health Center, was admitted for observation because of suspected new pneumonia.

The next morning, Yan Xiaowen was picked up by a car from the hospital and never returned. Xiao Wei, the youngest son of the same party, though asymptomatic, was also kept in the same ward for observation under the "close contact" quarantine, but because his brother Yan Cheng has no independent action, coupled with no abnormal symptoms, hospital beds and other conditions, so was left alone in isolation at home.

The separated Yan Xiaowen is anxious about Yan Cheng's condition, calling his second sister Yan Jirong to take care of Yan Cheng. At the same time, Yan Xiaowen also told the situation, "snail home" person in charge Zhu Wenqin, the latter through the parent organization channel to Hubei Disabled Federation report.

Yan called a village official, Yan Donghua, to ask for help after he was admitted to the hospital, according to a later official statement from the town of huajiahe in Hong'an County.

On New Year's Eve, two people take care of Yan Cheng

On Jan. 24, the day after Yan was quarantined in a hospital, he and Yan were moved to a designated quarantine facility in Hong'an County, the Xinghua Township Health Center.

On This Day, stay at home Yan Cheng had two meals. One meal was fed by Ergu Yan Jirong, and the other was fed by a staff member of the town health center named Jinhui.

This Day, Yanjia Village Committee Director Chen Jingyou, village deputy cadres Yan Donghua, Liu Jinzhou and other village cadres, village Doctor Xiong Tianming, second aunt Yan Jirong, have all come to see Yancheng.

According to Yan Jirong to rice and millet introduced, she was to Yan into a meal, also changed diapers.

According to the township government, when the village officials visited Yan Cheng, they brought oranges, cookies and took his temperature, which was 37 degrees Celsius.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The next day, on the first day of the Lunar New Year, Yan Jirong because of physical discomfort, no longer to take care of his nephew. Yan Cheng's first day of the year of the rat has not eaten, changed diapers, become a mystery.

According to the official account, the village committee arranged for Xiong Tianming, the village doctor, to attend to Yan Cheng's life that evening. But with no protective clothing, Tian Ming, worried about being infected, did not agree.

At the Xinghua Township Health Center, Yan Xiaowen, who had not received any messages from her children for a day, repeatedly called Chen Jingyou, the village committee director. In Wuhan, Zhu Wenqin also continued to call the disabled persons'Federation for help.

Yan Cheng has a fever

On the morning of January 26, Zhu Wenqin learned from the village committee director, Chen Jingyou, that Yan Cheng had a slight fever.

At 4:30 p.m. , Xiang Huarong, a nurse at Huajiahe Township Health Center, went to Feed Yan and take his temperature, according to an official statement. Around 6:00 pm, the town health workers to report to the higher-level Adult Yan temperature high.

At about 9 pm, Tao Weibo, the director of the town health center, Chen Jingyou, the village director, and others went to visit Yan Cheng and took his temperature. When they found that Yan Cheng had a fever, they immediately sent him to the town health center for a temperature check, blood test, film and other examinations. Meanwhile, Zhu Wenqin and Chen Jingyou two calls to understand the situation, and request to leave Yan Cheng in the hospital.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Yan Cheng's electrocardiogram at the township health center on Jan. 26

But "the town hospital, according to the examination results, believed that Yan did not constitute a condition to stay in the hospital for observation. " Yan's hospital also refused to admit him because he could not take care of himself, for fear of causing more infections.

Around 10 pm that night, Yan was sent home again.

In this way, Yan Cheng missed the chance to be admitted to the hospital.

On January 27th, five days after his separation from his father, Yan Cheng's care remained unresolved.

Dai Rong, director of the network of parents' organizations of Mentally Handicapped Persons, reported the matter to the China Disabled Persons' Federation, the Hubei Provincial Federation of Disabled Persons at all levels, the China Elite Association, the China Intellectual Association and other organizations, and set up the Wechat Group "help Hubei Hongan Dad" , trying to work together with the multi-force to solve the placement of Yan Cheng nursing problems.

At the same time, according to an official statement, on the same morning, the mayor of the town of Huahe called together the People's Federation of Disabled People, Civil Affairs, the village committee and other relevant personnel to study and deploy Yan Cheng's care work. The town health center was in charge of Yan Cheng's medical treatment, and the village committee arranged for special care, and request a protective suit for the orderlies. County Disabled People's Federation also sent Yan Cheng 1000 yuan sympathy gold and diapers and other supplies.

In the afternoon, Yan Xiaowen contact Chen Jingyou ask about the progress of nursing staff, Chen Jingyou said that spending money also can not find nursing staff, no protective clothing too big risk. Had come to take care of Yan Cheng's second aunt Yan Jirong also because still in the injection, can not go.

Until 7:30 pm, Chen Jingyou just informed Yan Xiaowen, nursing staff has been found. Feeling somewhat relieved, Yan Xiaowen posted a letter on his microblog asking for help with a protective suit for nursing staff.

As of 12:00 that evening, Yan Xiaowen and others do not know whether someone to Yan into the day feed things. But the huajiahe government later issued the statement, that afternoon, village Doctor Xiong Tianming and her husband together to Yan Cheng temperature, feeding.

120 more times. 110 more times

On January 28th, three days later, second aunt Yan Jirong went to Yan's home. Accompanying him is village Doctor Xiong Tianming. Without enough protective clothing, Yan entered the room wearing a mask and rubber gloves.

"As soon as I came in, I saw Yan Cheng with his head hanging over his bed, his face covered with vomit and his bedding soaked through. " Yan Jirong said that when he saw her come in, he shouted, "AH AH AH! ".

In the process of helping Yan Cheng Nursing Change, she found that Yan Cheng body some cold, later feed porridge, Yan Cheng only eat two. Yan Jirong feel not right, immediately tell the situation Yan Xiaowen.

That afternoon and evening, Yan Xiaowen, Zhu Wenqin and Nuan, another parent of snail homeland, called 120 and 110 in Hong'an County several times, both refused to admit Yan on the grounds that he was not a first aid patient, had reported to his superior, needed to report to the police in the village, and had no guardian.

Warm mother also called the village director Chen Jingyou, please call the police for help, Chen Jingyou give feedback is, "did not come, no place. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Here's a screenshot of the warm mom's call

According to the official statement and Yan Jirong's account, at noon on January 28, Yan Jirong Fed Yan Cheng a meal. At 3:30 p.m. and 9:00 p.m. , Chen Jingyou, the head of the village committee, led the nursing staff to the door twice, feeding Yan Cheng two cups of amino acids, because huajiahe township health center director said Amino acids mixed with hot water can ease Yan Cheng's vomiting.

Chen Jingyou on Wechat, a warm mother sent two photos, and a video chat with warm mother.

"On both occasions, I didn't see Yan's facial expression, nor did I know his temperature or mental state, " Nuan said.

And Huajiahe town official situation statement shows, Chen Jingyou and others to Yan Cheng measured the body temperature, see Yan Cheng "state is OK. ".

Later that night, Fine Arts Co Chair Wen Hong and Yan Xiaowen received word that tomorrow morning she could be sent to a local designated quarantine site for suspected personnel to be cared for by the Huajiahe town hospital.

Died at the quarantine site

At 11 a.m. on January 29, Dai Rong, who had been involved in the matter, sent a message to the editors of rice and millet, "At present, the child's body temperature is normal, new bedsheets and quilts and diapers have been delivered, and the town government, led by the mayor, has formed a care team to ensure that the child will be visited and cared for every day. "

Around 11:30, Huajiahe Township Health Center sent a car to pick up YAN CHENG TO FOCUS observation point. During the transfer, village officials also took photos and sent them to Yan Xiaowen.

The rescue wechat group that organizes for Yan resounds a jubilant and grateful voice. These for Yan Cheng to run six days of the national community of enthusiastic parents with mental retardation, finally ushered in the Dawn. "Yan Cheng is saved. "

Two and a half hours later, however, she received a call from the village council -- she was going to die.

According to the official statement, at about 12:30 on January 29, the paramedics found Cheng Yan with respiratory arrest, dilated pupils, and no pulse or heartbeat. Yan was pronounced dead at the scene.

Until the evening of Jan. 31, Yan and others had not been informed of the cause of Yan's death, nor had he or other relatives been notified of an official autopsy.

Authorities are demanding that the body be cremated as soon as possible

Yan Cheng after death, Yan Xiaowen to the hospital and the village committee, want to see the children immediately back to the last one. But it was not approved.

On January 30, Liu Changan, director of the Rehabilitation Department of the Disabled People's Federation of Hong'An County, Wang Baoquan, secretary of the Party Committee of Huajiahe Town, and Zhang Jian, director of the Civil Affairs Office of Huajiahe town, went to the health center to see Yan Xiaowen and offered to cremate his corpse.

"The three were wearing protective clothing, goggles and N95 masks, saying 'this is in accordance with the country's epidemic prevention and control instructions and regulations' . ". Yan said he was "under pressure" to issue a letter of entrustment to his uncle to cremate the body.

The power of attorney that Yan said he was forced to sign

But soon, with a friend's warning, Yan announced through the media that he was withdrawing the power of attorney and reissuing it, hoping to find a client to do two things for him:

1. Collect Yan Cheng's medical records from the hospital, transfer and copy medical records, and collect death certificates.

2. I would like to donate all of Yan Cheng's body and organs. If the body donation can not be carried out, the investigation team needs to wait for the results of the investigation, and then deal with the situation.

In the afternoon, the official financial media center in Hong'an County, Hubei Province, issued an update on the latest outbreak, confirming that Yan was suffering from COVID-19 pneumonia and saying that an investigation team had been set up to investigate Yan's death.

On January 30, Liu Xuerong, secretary of the Huanggang Municipal Party Committee, said in an interview with Hong'an County and other subordinate leaders that units and individuals who failed to implement the responsibility for epidemic prevention and control should be firmly punished by the punishment and should be removed from their posts, according to the Huanggang daily.

In response to Yan's death on Jan. 31, the Ministry of Civil Affairs said the documents had made it more clear that more care and support should be given to families whose members were being treated in isolation.

Did the son die of a viral infection, or was it something else? If his son had been brought to the hospital in time, would he have survived?

Yan Xiaowen, a patient with COVID-19 pneumonia in the hospital ward, still has no answer to the questions that surround him.

As of this date, 9,692 cases had been diagnosed and 213 had died, 15,238 suspected cases and 102427 close contacts were under medical surveillance in isolation.

- end of story.-thank you
